      "content": "You are a subagent: gsd-codebase-mapper. Your role is to investigate and produce structured analysis of a specific domain in the codebase. You MUST fulfill your task within boundaries without deviation.\n\n## YOUR TASK: Investigate Cluster B - PTY/Background Command System\n\nInvestigate the PTY and background command system in the Hivemind harness. This includes:\n\n### Files to investigate:\n1. `src/features/background-command/` — entire directory (pty/*.ts files)\n2. `src/tools/hivemind/run-background-command.ts` — the tool entry point\n3. `src/features/background-command/pty/pty-manager.ts`\n4. `src/features/background-command/pty/pty-runtime.ts`\n5. `src/features/background-command/pty/pty-buffer.ts`\n6. `src/features/background-command/pty/pty-types.ts`\n\n### Also check for any related planning docs:\n7. `docs/draft/` — any PTY-related draft docs\n8. `.planning/` — any CP-PTY phase documents (search for \"PTY\" or \"background\" in filenames)\n\n## WHAT TO PRODUCE:\n\n### A. For each source file, document:\n- Purpose (what it does, in 1-2 sentences)\n- Key types/interfaces defined\n- Key functions exported\n- Dependencies (imports)\n- LOC count\n- Whether it's actually functional or stub/placeholder\n\n### B. Tool analysis (`run-background-command`):\n- Full input schema (all arguments)\n- Output schema\n- Action routing: what actions does it support?\n- How does each action work?\n- What state does it manage?\n- How does it integrate with pty-manager?\n\n### C. PTY Architecture:\n- How is PTY lifecycle managed (create → use → terminate)?\n- What is the relationship between pty-manager, pty-runtime, and pty-buffer?\n- How does bun-pty integration work?\n- What is the fallback when bun-pty is not available?\n\n### D. Gap analysis:\n- What functionality is implemented vs planned?\n- Are there TODOs or stubs that indicate unfinished work?\n- How does this relate to the CP-PTY-00 spike mentioned in AGENTS.md?\n- What are the known limitations documented in code?\n\n### E. Integration with OpenCode:\n- How does this interact with OpenCode's innate bash/shell capabilities?\n- Does it conflict with or complement OpenCode's native command execution?\n- How does it integrate with the delegation system (delegate-task)?\n\n## CONSTRAINTS:\n- READ each file fully — do not skim\n- Track ALL imports and dependencies\n- Do NOT suggest fixes — only report facts\n- Return a structured report in markdown format\n- Note any references to external repos (opencode-pty, OMO) in comments or docs\n\n## SUCCESS METRICS:\n- Complete picture of PTY/background command architecture\n- Clear status of what's implemented vs planned\n- All tool actions documented with their behavior\n- Integration points with delegation system identified\n",
